 BLACK Leopards have confirmed the appointment of Kostadin Papic. The well-travelled coach recently parted ways with Hearts of Oak after just 79 days in charge of the Ghana Premier League giants. Leopards confirmed the return of the Serbian mentor as Technical Manager at the club to work along with coach Lehlohonolo Seema and Morgan Shivanbu. The club announced the news in a virtual press conference on Thursday afternoon. This will be Papic's second stint at the club. His lastÂ  stint seven years-ago, he was the head coach. The former Royal Eagles coach has signed a two-year contract with club. 